23/03/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A total of 64 per cent of the population supports efforts to join NATO, according to a poll by the Institute for Political, Sociological and Legal Research, published Friday (21 March). Some 21 per cent said they object to entering the Alliance, while 15 per cent said they had no opinion. From a total of 1,200 respondents, 17 per cent said they believe the country will accede very soon, while 49 per cent expect it will not happen in the near future. Nearly 19 per cent were absolutely pessimistic, saying membership aspirations would never be fulfilled. (Utrinski Vesnik - 22/03/03; MIA - 21/03/03)
